p.s:
Good, ſpeak to th' mariners: fall
to't yarely, or we run our ſelves a-ground;
beſtir, beſtir.

Hey, my hearts; cheerly, my hearts; yare,
yare; take in the top ſail; tend to th' maſter's whiſtle;
blow, 'till thou burſt thy wind, if room enough.

his forwad voice now is to ſpeak well of his friend;
his backward voice now is to ſpatter foul ſpeeches, and to de-
tract.

Thou lieſt, thou jeſting monkey, thou;
I would, my valiant maſter would deſtroy thee:
I do not lie.

Enter ſeveral ſtrange ſhapes, bringing in a ban-
quet; and dance about it with a gentle actions of ſalutation;
and, inviting the King, &c. to eat, they depart.
